value.0: Fashioned from rough iron, these bars extend into a narrow slot in the floor.

This chamber is almost painful in how foul the odors trapped within are, reaching a nauseating peak at the mouth of what appears to be a septic tunnel. The passage slopes down, inundated with a mixture of salt water, sewage, and swampy freshwater - although 'fresh' has no pleasant connotations here.

The tunnel seems to continue on for an indeterminate distance, and might be swim-able...

As the steps continued to ascend beyond the gate, the air becomes less eye-wateringly offensive and the tunnel seems better maintained. Briney water runs down the stairs in amounts that vary with civic and lunar tides, washing all manner of the city's refuse along with it.

Following the steps down enters into a stream of waste and water that flows sluggishly to the west and north. Oddly, there is an occasional draft that brings in the smell of cow and clear out the fumes, but it does nothing to improve the pervasive foulness of sewage and swamp.

The only permanent sources of light here seem to be near the tunnel leading up.

Value.value: This tunnel undoubtedly leads to the Lowlands Swamp northwest of Southport. You've heard that Trogs have taken up residence there and that they can be quite ferocious...
While not that familiar with the area, you think this tunnel may lead to the Lowlands Swamp, which you've heard is northwest of Southport. You've also heard it can be a dangerous place...

You're no expert on the area, but between the warning sign and the generally putrid state the water is in here, you can guess it's probably a bad idea to swim through here unless you know what you're doing...

Value.value: This is the work of a jelly, likely of the Ochre variety given the climate. They are notorious for multiplying when hit with sharp or pointed objects, or electrical energy.
Given the state of the body and the damp sewer climate, you're fairly certain this body is the work of a Jelly, notorious for multiplying when hit with sharp or pointed objects.
Whatever did this must have some sort of flesh-dissolving acid, because nothing could pick a body that clean with teeth alone.
